Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water (1 1⁄2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

== Pickled Cucumber ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine half the @White wine vinegar{5%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), 1⁄2 tsp sugar (1 tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt.

Trim ends from @cucumber{1}. Using a #peeler{}, shave cucumber lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the seedy core; discard core. Stir cucumber ribbons into bowl with vinegar mixture.

Set aside, tossing occasionally, until ready to serve.

== Cabbage and Carrots ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz}; cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and @pepper{}.

Transfer to a #plate{}.

== Ginger Beef ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @ground beef{10%oz} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in half the @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} (save the rest for serving) and remaining vinegar. Cook for ~{30%seconds}, then stir in @umami ginger sauce{4%oz}.

Bring to a simmer, then immediately turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

> Simply cook through this step as instructed, swapping in beef or turkey for pork.

== Sriracha Crema ==

While pork cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp} with @Sriracha{1%tsp} to taste. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with pork, cabbage and carrots, and pickled cucumber (draining first). Drizzle with Sriracha crema. Garnish with scallion greens and as many remaining sesame seeds as you like. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.